  "text": "A further major discrepancy is the RCP CH 4 time series, which differs strongly from all other sources. Emissions are significantly higher than in other sources but show a steep decline between 1990 and 2000. No other source used in this analysis shows this effect. RCP CH 4 emissions are based on [CITATION_1] , which uses EDGAR-HYDE but adds Table 10 . Uncertainties for gases and sectors covered in the PRIMAP-hist dataset. \"NA\" indicates that there are no emissions from this gas and sector combination. \"-\" indicates that we have no uncertainty estimate for the gas-sector combination. Where different uncertainty estimates exist, we calculate both upper and lower bound aggregate uncertainties. Calculations have been carried out according to the IPCC tier 1 methodology using average global emissions gas shares of the period 1990-2014. All calculated values are rounded to the nearest multiple of 5 % except for CO 2 values, which are rounded to 1 % with the exception of category 1, where rounding is to 0.1 %. For category 5 the high and low uncertainty cases are the same within rounding, so only one number is given. [CITATION_2] ; e calculated from available data for subsectors and gases; f estimated, no data available; g category 0 uncertainty value from b used.",
